{
  "video_id": "ylOlZz7s52Q",
  "title": "The tiny creature that secretly powers the planet | Penny Chisholm",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12760.0,
      "end_time": 15600.0,
      "text": "I'd like to introduce you to a tiny microorganism"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16880.0,
      "end_time": 18616.0,
      "text": "that you've probably never heard of:"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18640.0,
      "end_time": 20616.0,
      "text": "its name is Prochlorococcus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20640.0,
      "end_time": 22840.0,
      "text": "and it's really an amazing little being."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23680.0,
      "end_time": 26576.0,
      "text": "For one thing, its ancestors"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26600.0,
      "end_time": 30416.0,
      "text": "changed the earth in ways that made it possible for us to evolve,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30440.0,
      "end_time": 32496.0,
      "text": "and hidden in its genetic code"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32520.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34296.0,
      "text": "is a blueprint"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34320.0,
      "end_time": 39600.0,
      "text": "that may inspire ways to reduce our dependency on fossil fuel."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40480.0,
      "end_time": 42336.0,
      "text": "But the most amazing thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42360.0,
      "end_time": 44976.0,
      "text": "is that there are three billion billion billion"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 45000.0,
      "end_time": 46816.0,
      "text": "of these tiny cells on the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46840.0,
      "end_time": 50160.0,
      "text": "and we didn't know they existed until 35 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51280.0,
      "end_time": 52736.0,
      "text": "So to tell you their story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52760.0,
      "end_time": 55000.0,
      "text": "I need to first take you way back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55800.0,
      "end_time": 59419.0,
      "text": "four billion years ago, when the earth might have looked something like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 60480.0,
      "end_time": 62336.0,
      "text": "There was no life on the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 62360.0,
      "end_time": 64640.0,
      "text": "there was no oxygen in the atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 65319.0,
      "end_time": 70976.0,
      "text": "So what happened to change that planet into the one we enjoy today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 71000.0,
      "end_time": 72816.0,
      "text": "teeming with life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72840.0,
      "end_time": 74480.0,
      "text": "teeming with plants and animals?"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 75480.0,
      "end_time": 77760.0,
      "text": "Well, in a word, photosynthesis."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 79800.0,
      "end_time": 81176.0,
      "text": "About two and a half billion years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 81200.0,
      "end_time": 85136.0,
      "text": "some of these ancient ancestors of Prochlorococcus evolved"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 85160.0,
      "end_time": 87496.0,
      "text": "so that they could use solar energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 87520.0,
      "end_time": 88816.0,
      "text": "and absorb it"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 88840.0,
      "end_time": 93856.0,
      "text": "and split water into its component parts of oxygen and hydrogen."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 93880.0,
      "end_time": 96295.0,
      "text": "And they used the chemical energy produced"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 96320.0,
      "end_time": 100216.0,
      "text": "to draw CO2, carbon dioxide, out of the atmosphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 100240.0,
      "end_time": 104560.0,
      "text": "and use it to build sugars and proteins and amino acids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 104800.0,
      "end_time": 106480.0,
      "text": "all the things that life is made of."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 107560.0,
      "end_time": 110656.0,
      "text": "And as they evolved and grew more and more"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 110680.0,
      "end_time": 112736.0,
      "text": "over millions and millions of years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 112760.0,
      "end_time": 115840.0,
      "text": "that oxygen accumulated in the atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117480.0,
      "end_time": 119976.0,
      "text": "Until about 500 million years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 120000.0,
      "end_time": 123696.0,
      "text": "there was enough in the atmosphere that larger organisms could evolve."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 123720.0,
      "end_time": 125656.0,
      "text": "There was an explosion of life-forms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 125680.0,
      "end_time": 128240.0,
      "text": "and, ultimately, we appeared on the scene."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 129000.0,
      "end_time": 130320.0,
      "text": "While that was going on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 131440.0,
      "end_time": 134656.0,
      "text": "some of those ancient photosynthesizers died"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 134680.0,
      "end_time": 136360.0,
      "text": "and were compressed and buried,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137160.0,
      "end_time": 139256.0,
      "text": "and became fossil fuel"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 139280.0,
      "end_time": 143416.0,
      "text": "with sunlight buried in their carbon bonds."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143440.0,
      "end_time": 148120.0,
      "text": "They're basically buried sunlight in the form of coal and oil."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 149800.0,
      "end_time": 150656.0,
      "text": "Today's photosynthesizers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 150680.0,
      "end_time": 156336.0,
      "text": "their engines are descended from those ancient microbes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 156360.0,
      "end_time": 159600.0,
      "text": "and they feed basically all of life on earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 160440.0,
      "end_time": 163776.0,
      "text": "Your heart is beating using the solar energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 163800.0,
      "end_time": 166160.0,
      "text": "that some plant processed for you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 166400.0,
      "end_time": 168456.0,
      "text": "and the stuff your body is made out of"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 168480.0,
      "end_time": 170960.0,
      "text": "is made out of CO2"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 170120.0,
      "end_time": 172560.0,
      "text": "that some plant processed for you."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 173480.0,
      "end_time": 177760.0,
      "text": "Basically, we're all made out of sunlight and carbon dioxide."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 178640.0,
      "end_time": 180696.0,
      "text": "Fundamentally, we're just hot air."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 180720.0,
      "end_time": 183400.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 184560.0,
      "end_time": 186256.0,
      "text": "So as terrestrial beings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 186280.0,
      "end_time": 189336.0,
      "text": "we're very familiar with the plants on land:"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 189360.0,
      "end_time": 193976.0,
      "text": "the trees, the grasses, the pastures, the crops."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 194000.0,
      "end_time": 197816.0,
      "text": "But the oceans are filled with billions of tons of animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 197840.0,
      "end_time": 200200.0,
      "text": "Do you ever wonder what's feeding them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 201400.0,
      "end_time": 203776.0,
      "text": "Well there's an invisible pasture"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 203800.0,
      "end_time": 207576.0,
      "text": "of microscopic photosynthesizers called phytoplankton"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 207600.0,
      "end_time": 210239.0,
      "text": "that fill the upper 200 meters of the ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 212000.0,
      "end_time": 215416.0,
      "text": "and they feed the entire open ocean ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 215440.0,
      "end_time": 217856.0,
      "text": "Some of the animals live among them and eat them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 217880.0,
      "end_time": 220416.0,
      "text": "and others swim up to feed on them at night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 220440.0,
      "end_time": 224416.0,
      "text": "while others sit in the deep and wait for them to die and settle down"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 224440.0,
      "end_time": 225964.0,
      "text": "and then they chow down on them."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 227320.0,
      "end_time": 230416.0,
      "text": "So these tiny phytoplankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 230440.0,
      "end_time": 234576.0,
      "text": "collectively, weigh less than one percent of all the plants on land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 234600.0,
      "end_time": 238896.0,
      "text": "but annually they photosynthesize as much as all of the plants on land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 238920.0,
      "end_time": 241335.0,
      "text": "including the Amazon rainforest"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 241360.0,
      "end_time": 243560.0,
      "text": "that we consider the lungs of the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 244280.0,
      "end_time": 248256.0,
      "text": "Every year, they fix 50 billion tons of carbon"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 248280.0,
      "end_time": 251536.0,
      "text": "in the form of carbon dioxide into their bodies"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 251560.0,
      "end_time": 254240.0,
      "text": "that feeds the ocean ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 255120.0,
      "end_time": 257696.0,
      "text": "How does this tiny amount of biomass"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 257720.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259776.00000000003,
      "text": "produce as much as all the plants on land?"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 259800.0,
      "end_time": 262336.0,
      "text": "Well, they don't have trunks and stems"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 262360.0,
      "end_time": 265296.0,
      "text": "and flowers and fruits and all that to maintain."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 265320.0,
      "end_time": 268135.0,
      "text": "All they have to do is grow and divide and grow and divide."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 268160.0,
      "end_time": 271760.0,
      "text": "They're really lean little photosynthesis machines."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 273519.0,
      "end_time": 274720.0,
      "text": "They really crank."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 279400.0,
      "end_time": 283296.0,
      "text": "So there are thousands of different species of phytoplankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 283320.0,
      "end_time": 285496.0,
      "text": "come in all different shapes and sizes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 285520.0,
      "end_time": 288775.0,
      "text": "all roughly less than the width of a human hair."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 288800.0,
      "end_time": 292376.0,
      "text": "Here, I'm showing you some of the more beautiful ones,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 292400.0,
      "end_time": 293880.0,
      "text": "the textbook versions."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 294640.0,
      "end_time": 297880.0,
      "text": "I call them the charismatic species of phytoplankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 300120.0,
      "end_time": 303120.0,
      "text": "And here is Prochlorococcus."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 304120.0,
      "end_time": 305656.0,
      "text": "I know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 305680.0,
      "end_time": 308616.0,
      "text": "it just looks like a bunch of schmutz on a microscope slide."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 308640.0,
      "end_time": 310216.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 310240.0,
      "end_time": 312560.0,
      "text": "But they're in there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 312800.0,
      "end_time": 314840.0,
      "text": "and I'm going to reveal them to you in a minute."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 315560.0,
      "end_time": 319120.0,
      "text": "But first I want to tell you how they were discovered."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 320800.0,
      "end_time": 322216.0,
      "text": "About 38 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 322240.0,
      "end_time": 327160.0,
      "text": "we were playing around with a technology in my lab called flow cytometry"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 327400.0,
      "end_time": 331520.0,
      "text": "that was developed for biomedical research for studying cells like cancer cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 333800.0,
      "end_time": 336376.0,
      "text": "but it turns out we were using it for this off-label purpose"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 336400.0,
      "end_time": 340359.0,
      "text": "which was to study phytoplankton, and it was beautifully suited to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 341480.0,
      "end_time": 343256.0,
      "text": "And here's how it works:"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 343280.0,
      "end_time": 346520.0,
      "text": "so you inject a sample in this tiny little capillary tube,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 347840.0,
      "end_time": 351335.0,
      "text": "and the cells go single file by a laser,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 351360.0,
      "end_time": 355416.0,
      "text": "and as they do, they scatter light according to their size"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 355440.0,
      "end_time": 359960.0,
      "text": "and they emit light according to whatever pigments they might have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 359120.0,
      "end_time": 361736.0,
      "text": "whether they're natural or whether you stain them."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 361760.0,
      "end_time": 364120.0,
      "text": "And the chlorophyl of phytoplankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 365160.0,
      "end_time": 366496.0,
      "text": "which is green,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 366520.0,
      "end_time": 370256.0,
      "text": "emits red light when you shine blue light on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 370280.0,
      "end_time": 373496.0,
      "text": "And so we used this instrument for several years"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 373520.0,
      "end_time": 375335.0,
      "text": "to study our phytoplankton cultures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 375360.0,
      "end_time": 378976.0,
      "text": "species like those charismatic ones that I showed you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 379000.0,
      "end_time": 381200.0,
      "text": "just studying their basic cell biology."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 382160.0,
      "end_time": 385960.0,
      "text": "But all that time, we thought, well wouldn't it be really cool"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 385120.0,
      "end_time": 387936.0,
      "text": "if we could take an instrument like this out on a ship"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 387960.0,
      "end_time": 389656.0,
      "text": "and just squirt seawater through it"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 389680.0,
      "end_time": 394416.0,
      "text": "and see what all those diversity of phytoplankton would look like."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 394440.0,
      "end_time": 396536.0,
      "text": "So I managed to get my hands"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 396560.0,
      "end_time": 399776.0,
      "text": "on what we call a big rig in flow cytometry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 399800.0,
      "end_time": 402240.0,
      "text": "a large, powerful laser"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 403240.0,
      "end_time": 405976.0,
      "text": "with a money-back guarantee from the company"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 406000.0,
      "end_time": 408936.0,
      "text": "that if it didn't work on a ship, they would take it back."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 408960.0,
      "end_time": 411976.0,
      "text": "And so a young scientist that I was working with at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 412000.0,
      "end_time": 414576.0,
      "text": "Rob Olson, was able to take this thing apart,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 414600.0,
      "end_time": 418456.0,
      "text": "put it on a ship, put it back together and take it off to sea."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 418480.0,
      "end_time": 419816.0,
      "text": "And it worked like a charm."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 419840.0,
      "end_time": 422976.0,
      "text": "We didn't think it would, because we thought the ship's vibrations"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 423000.0,
      "end_time": 425376.0,
      "text": "would get in the way of the focusing of the laser,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 425400.0,
      "end_time": 427560.0,
      "text": "but it really worked like a charm."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 427800.0,
      "end_time": 430575.0,
      "text": "And so we mapped the phytoplankton distributions across the ocean."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 430600.0,
      "end_time": 434216.0,
      "text": "For the first time, you could look at them one cell at a time in real time"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 434240.0,
      "end_time": 437560.0,
      "text": "and see what was going on -- that was very exciting."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 437800.0,
      "end_time": 440960.0,
      "text": "But one day, Rob noticed some faint signals"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 440120.0,
      "end_time": 441616.0,
      "text": "coming out of the instrument"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 441640.0,
      "end_time": 445336.0,
      "text": "that we dismissed as electronic noise"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 445360.0,
      "end_time": 447656.0,
      "text": "for probably a year"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 447680.0,
      "end_time": 451160.0,
      "text": "before we realized that it wasn't really behaving like noise."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 451400.0,
      "end_time": 453200.0,
      "text": "It had some regular patterns to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 454440.0,
      "end_time": 455880.0,
      "text": "To make a long story short,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 456640.0,
      "end_time": 459176.0,
      "text": "it was tiny, tiny little cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 459200.0,
      "end_time": 462575.0,
      "text": "less than one-one hundredth the width of a human hair"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 462600.0,
      "end_time": 464416.0,
      "text": "that contain chlorophyl."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 464440.0,
      "end_time": 465800.0,
      "text": "That was Prochlorococcus."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 467400.0,
      "end_time": 469800.0,
      "text": "So remember this slide that I showed you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 470680.0,
      "end_time": 473296.0,
      "text": "If you shine blue light on that same sample,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 473320.0,
      "end_time": 474520.0,
      "text": "this is what you see:"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 475280.0,
      "end_time": 479135.0,
      "text": "two tiny little red light-emitting cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 479160.0,
      "end_time": 481280.0,
      "text": "Those are Prochlorococcus."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 482760.0,
      "end_time": 486800.0,
      "text": "They are the smallest and most abundant photosynthetic cell on the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 489710.0,
      "end_time": 490976.0,
      "text": "At first, we didn't know what they were,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 491000.0,
      "end_time": 492776.0,
      "text": "so we called the \"little greens.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 492800.0,
      "end_time": 494776.0,
      "text": "It was a very affectionate name for them."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 494800.0,
      "end_time": 498416.0,
      "text": "Ultimately, we knew enough about them to give them the name Prochlorococcus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 498440.0,
      "end_time": 500656.0,
      "text": "which means \"primitive green berry.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 500680.0,
      "end_time": 502120.0,
      "text": "And it was about that time"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 503480.0,
      "end_time": 506256.0,
      "text": "that I became so smitten by these little cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 506280.0,
      "end_time": 510400.0,
      "text": "that I redirected my entire lab to study them and nothing else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 511760.0,
      "end_time": 514775.0,
      "text": "and my loyalty to them has really paid off."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 514799.0,
      "end_time": 518359.0,
      "text": "They've given me a tremendous amount, including bringing me here."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 519880.0,
      "end_time": 525240.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 525799.0,
      "end_time": 528775.0,
      "text": "So over the years, we and others, many others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 528799.0,
      "end_time": 532175.0,
      "text": "have studied Prochlorococcus across the oceans"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 532200.0,
      "end_time": 536776.0,
      "text": "and found that they're very abundant over wide, wide ranges"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 536800.0,
      "end_time": 538439.0,
      "text": "in the open ocean ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 539680.0,
      "end_time": 543776.0,
      "text": "They're particularly abundant in what are called the open ocean gyres."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 543800.0,
      "end_time": 547536.0,
      "text": "These are sometimes referred to as the deserts of the oceans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 547560.0,
      "end_time": 549575.0,
      "text": "but they're not deserts at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 549600.0,
      "end_time": 552136.0,
      "text": "Their deep blue water is teeming"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 552160.0,
      "end_time": 555560.0,
      "text": "with a hundred million Prochlorococcus cells per liter."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 556360.0,
      "end_time": 558976.0,
      "text": "If you crowd them together like we do in our cultures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 559000.0,
      "end_time": 562536.0,
      "text": "you can see their beautiful green chlorophyl."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 562560.0,
      "end_time": 567175.0,
      "text": "One of those test tubes has a billion Prochlorococcus in it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 567200.0,
      "end_time": 568656.0,
      "text": "and as I told you earlier,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 568680.0,
      "end_time": 571856.0,
      "text": "there are three billion billion billion of them on the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 571880.0,
      "end_time": 574960.0,
      "text": "That's three octillion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 574120.0,
      "end_time": 575800.0,
      "text": "if you care to convert."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 576480.0,
      "end_time": 578176.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 578200.0,
      "end_time": 582960.0,
      "text": "And collectively, they weigh more than the human population"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 582120.0,
      "end_time": 586800.0,
      "text": "and they photosynthesize as much as all of the crops on land."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 587800.0,
      "end_time": 590520.0,
      "text": "They're incredibly important in the global ocean."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 591120.0,
      "end_time": 593616.0,
      "text": "So over the years, as we were studying them"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 593640.0,
      "end_time": 595816.0,
      "text": "and found how abundant they were,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 595840.0,
      "end_time": 597776.0,
      "text": "we thought, hmm, this is really strange."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 597800.0,
      "end_time": 601640.0,
      "text": "How can a single species be so abundant across so many different habitats?"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 602640.0,
      "end_time": 604656.0,
      "text": "And as we isolated more into culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 604680.0,
      "end_time": 606815.0,
      "text": "we learned that they are different ecotypes."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 606840.0,
      "end_time": 609736.0,
      "text": "There are some that are adapted to the high-light intensities"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 609760.0,
      "end_time": 611160.0,
      "text": "in the surface water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 611400.0,
      "end_time": 614616.0,
      "text": "and there are some that are adapted to the low light in the deep ocean."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 614640.0,
      "end_time": 618216.0,
      "text": "In fact, those cells that live in the bottom of the sunlit zone"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 618240.0,
      "end_time": 623160.0,
      "text": "are the most efficient photosynthesizers of any known cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 623400.0,
      "end_time": 625376.0,
      "text": "And then we learned that there are some strains"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 625400.0,
      "end_time": 628816.0,
      "text": "that grow optimally along the equator,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 628840.0,
      "end_time": 630576.0,
      "text": "where there are higher temperatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 630600.0,
      "end_time": 632976.0,
      "text": "and some that do better at the cooler temperatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 633000.0,
      "end_time": 634256.0,
      "text": "as you go north and south."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 634280.0,
      "end_time": 637976.0,
      "text": "So as we studied these more and more and kept finding more and more diversity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 638000.0,
      "end_time": 640440.0,
      "text": "we thought, oh my God, how diverse are these things?"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 641400.0,
      "end_time": 644295.0,
      "text": "And about that time, it became possible to sequence their genomes"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 644320.0,
      "end_time": 647920.0,
      "text": "and really look under the hood and look at their genetic makeup."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 649280.0,
      "end_time": 653696.0,
      "text": "And we've been able to sequence the genomes of cultures that we have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 653720.0,
      "end_time": 656960.0,
      "text": "but also recently, using flow cytometry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 656120.0,
      "end_time": 658976.0,
      "text": "we can isolate individual cells from the wild"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 659000.0,
      "end_time": 661176.0,
      "text": "and sequence their individual genomes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 661200.0,
      "end_time": 664800.0,
      "text": "and now we've sequenced hundreds of Prochlorococcus."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 664840.0,
      "end_time": 668776.0,
      "text": "And although each cell has roughly 2,000 genes --"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 668800.0,
      "end_time": 672376.0,
      "text": "that's one tenth the size of the human genome --"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 672400.0,
      "end_time": 673856.0,
      "text": "as you sequence more and more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 673880.0,
      "end_time": 678576.0,
      "text": "you find that they only have a thousand of those in common"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 678600.0,
      "end_time": 681696.0,
      "text": "and the other thousand for each individual strain"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 681720.0,
      "end_time": 684296.0,
      "text": "is drawn from an enormous gene pool,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 684320.0,
      "end_time": 690936.0,
      "text": "and it reflects the particular environment that the cell might have thrived in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 690960.0,
      "end_time": 693936.0,
      "text": "not just high or low light or high or low temperature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 693960.0,
      "end_time": 696736.0,
      "text": "but whether there are nutrients that limit them"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 696760.0,
      "end_time": 699216.0,
      "text": "like nitrogen, phosphorus or iron."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 699240.0,
      "end_time": 701760.0,
      "text": "It reflects the habitat that they come from."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 702400.0,
      "end_time": 703600.0,
      "text": "Think of it this way."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 705400.0,
      "end_time": 708295.0,
      "text": "If each cell is a smartphone"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 708320.0,
      "end_time": 710240.0,
      "text": "and the apps are the genes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 711800.0,
      "end_time": 714536.0,
      "text": "when you get your smartphone, it comes with these built-in apps."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 714560.0,
      "end_time": 717776.0,
      "text": "Those are the ones that you can't delete if you're an iPhone person."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 717800.0,
      "end_time": 720856.0,
      "text": "You press on them and they don't jiggle and they don't have x's."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 720880.0,
      "end_time": 723496.0,
      "text": "Even if you don't want them, you can't get rid of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 723520.0,
      "end_time": 726960.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 726120.0,
      "end_time": 729256.0,
      "text": "Those are like the core genes of Prochlorococcus."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 729280.0,
      "end_time": 731336.0,
      "text": "They're the essence of the phone."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 731360.0,
      "end_time": 736336.0,
      "text": "But you have a huge pool of apps to draw upon"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 736360.0,
      "end_time": 742960.0,
      "text": "to make your phone custom-designed for your particular lifestyle and habitat."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 742120.0,
      "end_time": 745936.0,
      "text": "If you travel a lot, you'll have a lot of travel apps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 745960.0,
      "end_time": 750776.0,
      "text": "if you're into financial things, you might have a lot of financial apps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 750800.0,
      "end_time": 752335.0,
      "text": "or if you're like me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 752360.0,
      "end_time": 754296.0,
      "text": "you probably have a lot of weather apps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 754320.0,
      "end_time": 756936.0,
      "text": "hoping one of them will tell you what you want to hear."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 756960.0,
      "end_time": 758296.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 758320.0,
      "end_time": 760696.0,
      "text": "And I've learned the last couple days in Vancouver"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 760720.0,
      "end_time": 763696.0,
      "text": "that you don't need a weather app -- you just need an umbrella."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 763720.0,
      "end_time": 764936.0,
      "text": "So --"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 764960.0,
      "end_time": 767136.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 767160.0,
      "end_time": 769856.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 769880.0,
      "end_time": 775816.0,
      "text": "So just as your smartphone tells us something about how you live your life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 775840.0,
      "end_time": 777136.0,
      "text": "your lifestyle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 777160.0,
      "end_time": 779776.0,
      "text": "reading the genome of a Prochlorococcus cell"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 779800.0,
      "end_time": 783839.0,
      "text": "tells us what the pressures are in its environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 784680.0,
      "end_time": 786656.0,
      "text": "It's like reading its diary,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 786680.0,
      "end_time": 790455.0,
      "text": "not only telling us how it got through its day or its week,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 790480.0,
      "end_time": 793160.0,
      "text": "but even its evolutionary history."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 794200.0,
      "end_time": 797416.0,
      "text": "As we studied -- I said we've sequenced hundreds of these cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 797440.0,
      "end_time": 799296.0,
      "text": "and we can now project"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 799320.0,
      "end_time": 803456.0,
      "text": "what is the total genetic size --"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 803480.0,
      "end_time": 804696.0,
      "text": "gene pool --"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 804720.0,
      "end_time": 808216.0,
      "text": "of the Prochlorococcus federation, as we call it."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 808240.0,
      "end_time": 809896.0,
      "text": "It's like a superorganism."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 809920.0,
      "end_time": 812536.0,
      "text": "And it turns out that projections are"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 812560.0,
      "end_time": 815575.0,
      "text": "that the collective has 80,000 genes."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 815600.0,
      "end_time": 818536.0,
      "text": "That's four times the size of the human genome."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 818560.0,
      "end_time": 822976.0,
      "text": "And it's that diversity of gene pools"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 823000.0,
      "end_time": 825160.0,
      "text": "that makes it possible for them"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 825400.0,
      "end_time": 827295.0,
      "text": "to dominate these large regions of the oceans"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 827320.0,
      "end_time": 829560.0,
      "text": "and maintain their stability"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 829800.0,
      "end_time": 831000.0,
      "text": "year in and year out."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 832680.0,
      "end_time": 835856.0,
      "text": "So when I daydream about Prochlorococcus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 835880.0,
      "end_time": 838336.0,
      "text": "which I probably do more than is healthy --"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 838360.0,
      "end_time": 840560.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 840800.0,
      "end_time": 843456.0,
      "text": "I imagine them floating out there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 843480.0,
      "end_time": 844776.0,
      "text": "doing their job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 844800.0,
      "end_time": 846335.0,
      "text": "maintaining the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 846360.0,
      "end_time": 849536.0,
      "text": "feeding the animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 849560.0,
      "end_time": 851736.0,
      "text": "But also I inevitably end up"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 851760.0,
      "end_time": 855176.0,
      "text": "thinking about what a masterpiece they are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 855200.0,
      "end_time": 859960.0,
      "text": "finely tuned by millions of years of evolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 859120.0,
      "end_time": 861120.0,
      "text": "With 2,000 genes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 861960.0,
      "end_time": 864416.0,
      "text": "they can do what all of our human ingenuity"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 864440.0,
      "end_time": 866696.0,
      "text": "has not figured out how to do yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 866720.0,
      "end_time": 869696.0,
      "text": "They can take solar energy, CO2"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 869720.0,
      "end_time": 873216.0,
      "text": "and turn it into chemical energy in the form of organic carbon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 873240.0,
      "end_time": 876520.0,
      "text": "locking that sunlight in those carbon bonds."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 877760.0,
      "end_time": 881295.0,
      "text": "If we could figure out exactly how they do this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 881320.0,
      "end_time": 884336.0,
      "text": "it could inspire designs"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 884360.0,
      "end_time": 887296.0,
      "text": "that could reduce our dependency on fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 887320.0,
      "end_time": 890120.0,
      "text": "which brings my story full circle."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 891160.0,
      "end_time": 894550.0,
      "text": "The fossil fuels that are buried that we're burning"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 894800.0,
      "end_time": 898896.0,
      "text": "took millions of years for the earth to bury those,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 898920.0,
      "end_time": 901935.0,
      "text": "including those ancestors of Prochlorococcus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 901960.0,
      "end_time": 904856.0,
      "text": "and we're burning that now in the blink of an eye"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 904880.0,
      "end_time": 906816.0,
      "text": "on geological timescales."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 906840.0,
      "end_time": 909736.0,
      "text": "Carbon dioxide is increasing in the atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 909760.0,
      "end_time": 911336.0,
      "text": "It's a greenhouse gas."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 911360.0,
      "end_time": 913456.0,
      "text": "The oceans are starting to warm."
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 913480.0,
      "end_time": 916216.0,
      "text": "So the question is, what is that going to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 916240.0,
      "end_time": 918736.0,
      "text": "for my Prochlorococcus?"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 918760.0,
      "end_time": 923696.0,
      "text": "And I'm sure you're expecting me to say that my beloved microbes are doomed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 923720.0,
      "end_time": 925400.0,
      "text": "but in fact they're not."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 925960.0,
      "end_time": 931616.0,
      "text": "Projections are that their populations will expand as the ocean warms"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 931640.0,
      "end_time": 935520.0,
      "text": "to 30 percent larger by the year 2100."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 936000.0,
      "end_time": 937400.0,
      "text": "Does that make me happy?"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 938320.0,
      "end_time": 940976.0,
      "text": "Well, it makes me happy for Prochlorococcus of course --"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 941000.0,
      "end_time": 943296.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 943320.0,
      "end_time": 945720.0,
      "text": "but not for the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 946480.0,
      "end_time": 947856.0,
      "text": "There are winners and losers"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 947880.0,
      "end_time": 951136.0,
      "text": "in this global experiment that we've undertaken,"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 951160.0,
      "end_time": 954136.0,
      "text": "and it's projected that among the losers"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 954160.0,
      "end_time": 956216.0,
      "text": "will be some of those larger phytoplankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 956240.0,
      "end_time": 957536.0,
      "text": "those charismatic ones"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 957560.0,
      "end_time": 960376.0,
      "text": "which are expected to be reduced in numbers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 960400.0,
      "end_time": 963896.0,
      "text": "and they're the ones that feed the zooplankton that feed the fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 963920.0,
      "end_time": 965319.0,
      "text": "that we like to harvest."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 968600.0,
      "end_time": 973560.0,
      "text": "So Prochlorococcus has been my muse for the past 35 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 973800.0,
      "end_time": 975456.0,
      "text": "but there are legions of other microbes out there"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 975480.0,
      "end_time": 977640.0,
      "text": "maintaining our planet for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 978360.0,
      "end_time": 980416.0,
      "text": "They're out there"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 980440.0,
      "end_time": 984696.0,
      "text": "ready and waiting for us to find them so they can tell their stories, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 984720.0,
      "end_time": 985936.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 985960.0,
      "end_time": 991560.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}